  <prompt>
    Apply the design from task 030 to `INodeExecutor`. Add the `GetConfigSchema()` method, declare the
    `ExecutorConfigSchema` + `ConfigFieldDescriptor` record types in a co-located file, and provide a
    default placeholder return shape that prevents the interface addition from breaking every existing
    implementation. The 33 executor implementations get real implementations in task 032 — this task
    only opens the seam.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer. Mirror the existing INodeExecutor member style (XML doc, naming
    conventions). Do NOT over-engineer — no factories, no extension methods, no abstract base class.
  </role>

  <goal>
    1. `INodeExecutor` interface gains a new method `ExecutorConfigSchema GetConfigSchema()` (or per task 030 design)
    2. New record types `ExecutorConfigSchema` + `ConfigFieldDescriptor` exist in a new file `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/ExecutorConfigSchema.cs` (or as nested types per task 030 decision)
    3. Either: (a) interface method is a `virtual` default returning an empty placeholder `ExecutorConfigSchema(Fields: empty dictionary)`, OR (b) all 33 existing executors get a one-line `return new ExecutorConfigSchema(...)` stub. Pick per task 030 design.
    4. Build passes: 0 errors. Tests pass.
    5. No behavior change — existing executors continue to work unchanged.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-doc">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/getconfigschema-design.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
