    <file purpose="bff-constraints">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — method goes on `INodeExecutor` directly. No `IConfigSchemaProvider` abstraction.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — interface change is additive, NOT a new dispatch axis.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF Publish Hygiene — verify publish-size delta at task 036; this single interface + record addition should be ~0 KB.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — interface change is testable via the impl unit tests in task 034. No need to mock the interface here.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Component justification triple satisfied by task 030 design doc. This task implements that decision.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist applies. Placement decision: keep IN BFF — `ExecutorConfigSchema` lives next to its consumer `INodeExecutor`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F.1">No conditional DI registration added in this task — does not trigger asymmetric-registration anti-pattern.</constraint>
    <constraint source="DO NOT BREAK">All 33 existing `*NodeExecutor.cs` files MUST still compile after this change. Choose default-implementation OR stub-each-executor per task 030 — both paths are acceptable, but the build MUST pass.</constraint>
  </constraints>

